  "instructions": [
    "Combine shio-cure vegetables, onions, garlic, and rosemary in a large bowl.",
    "In a separate saucepan, heat olive oil over low heat.",
    "Add rum to the saucepan and ignite, allowing the flames to burn off the excess liquid.",
    "Remove from heat and stir in salt, black pepper, and lemon juice.",
    "Transfer the vegetable mixture to a clay or ceramic tagine or Dutch oven and spoon the labneh cheese over the top.",
    "Drizzle with pomegranate molasses and sprinkle with parsley.",
    "Cover and let ferment in the refrigerator for at least 24 hours or up to 3 days.",
    "Preheat oven to 375\u00184f (190\u00184c).",
    "Transfer the tagine to the oven and bake for 20 minutes, or until the cheese is melted and bubbly.",
    "Serve warm, garnished with additional parsley if desired."
  ],
